### CSS Attribute Selectors

Style elements based on their **attributes** and attribute **values**.

---

### Basic Attribute Selectors

| Selector | Example | Targets |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `[attr]` | `[target]` | Elements with the attribute |
| `[attr="value"]` | `[type="text"]` | Exact value match |
| `[attr~="value"]` | `[class~="logo"]` | Word in space-separated list |
| `[attr|="value"]` | `[lang|="en"]` | Value or value- (with dash) |

---

### Substring Attribute Selectors

| Selector | Meaning | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `[attr^="val"]` | Starts with | `[href^="https"]` |
| `[attr$="val"]` | Ends with | `[src$=".jpg"]` |
| `[attr*="val"]` | Contains | `[class*="btn"]` |

---

### Examples

```css
/* Exact match */
input[type="text"] {
  border: 1px solid blue;
}

/* Starts with */
a[href^="https"] {
  color: green;
}

/* Ends with */
img[src$=".png"] {
  border: 2px solid gray;
}

/* Contains */
[class*="icon"] {
  width: 24px;
  height: 24px;
}

/* Attribute present */
[disabled] {
  opacity: 0.5;
}
```

---

### Case-Insensitive

```css
/* Add i at end for case-insensitive */
[type="submit" i] {
  background: blue;
}
```

Matches `submit`, `SUBMIT`, `Submit`, etc.

---

> **Best Practice:** Use attribute selectors to style form inputs by type or links by protocol.
